  "title": "Pharmacy Technician, (NUHS@Home)*(5596)",
  "description": "<p>Pharmacy Technician (For NUHS@Home)</p>\n<p><strong>The incumbent is responsible to:</strong></p>\n<p>*  Assist the pharmacist in the processing of medication orders for dispensing which includes typing, packing, labelling and distribution of drug supplies.</p>\n<p>*  Perform billing functions and ensure that cost and revenue of all stocks supplied are recovered, if required</p>\n<p>*  Counsel medicines under the supervision of a pharmacist over tele-consult</p>\n<p>*  Monitor and maintain inventory stock level of drugs in the areas of work</p>\n<p>*  Receive, unpack and check deliveries against the appropriate documents, to ensure that items supplied are correct and accounted for</p>\n<p>*  Perform stock receipts and issues strictly in FIFO order</p>\n<p>*  Assist in providing quality customer service</p>\n<p>*  Maintains the cleanliness of the work areas and prepare these for daily operations</p>\n<p>*  Assist in orientating new staff assigned to the section</p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>*  Diploma in Pharmaceutical Science and relevant experience</p>\n<p>*  Able to work staggered shift duties Job</p>\n<p>*  Able to work weekends (half day morning)</p>\n<p>*  May need to travel out of NUH to remote sites in the west</p>",
